  "prompt": "Personal Productivity: Is there a service that allows bookmarking of quotes?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several services and tools that allow you to bookmark and organize quotes for personal productivity and reference. Here are some popular ones:\n\n1. **Evernote** - A versatile note-taking app that allows you to clip web pages, save quotes, and organize them with tags and notebooks. You can easily search through your saved quotes and notes.\n\n2. **Notion** - This is an all-in-one workspace application that can be tailored to save and organize quotes. You can create a dedicated page or database for quotes and use tags or categories to keep them organized.\n\n3. **Pocket** - Originally designed for saving and bookmarking articles, Pocket allows you to highlight and save specific quotes from web pages. You can tag your saved content for easy retrieval later.\n\n4. **OneNote** - Microsoft's note-taking application that is part of the Office suite. It provides a flexible layout for saving and organizing quotes, and you can sync your notes across devices.\n\n5. **Diigo** - A social bookmarking tool that lets you save web pages and annotate them. You can highlight text directly on web pages and organize your findings with tags and lists.\n\n6. **Raindrop.io** - A modern bookmarking tool that lets you save various content, including quotes. It provides organizational features like collections and tags to categorize your quotes.\n\n7. **Readwise** - This service is designed specifically for organizing and reviewing highlights and quotes from ebooks, articles, and web pages. It integrates with Kindle, Instapaper, Pocket, and more, allowing you to consolidate and manage your highlighted content.\n\nEach of these services has its own unique features, so you may want to explore a few to find the one that best fits your needs for storing and organizing quotes.",
